# Git Commit Identity

When creating git commits in this repository:

- **Author**: `Iman Suherman <iman.suherman@gmail.com>`
- **Committer**: `Iman Suherman <iman.suherman@gmail.com>`
- **Never** add `Co-authored-by` trailers or any other co-author attribution unless the user explicitly requests it.
- **Never** add `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` or any Cursor/agent attribution.
- **Never** use, reference, or leave traces of `suherman@qantas.com` in commit messages, author fields, or trailers.

Always pass explicit author and committer env vars on every commit. Do not rely on the environment default identity and do not run `git config` to change identity.

```bash
GIT_COMMITTER_NAME="Iman Suherman" \
GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL="iman.suherman@gmail.com" \
git commit --author="Iman Suherman <iman.suherman@gmail.com>" -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
Commit message here.

EOF
)"
```

Before finishing any task that creates commits, verify the latest commit message does not contain `Co-authored-by`.

If history needs cleaning, run:

```bash
GIT_SEQUENCE_EDITOR=true git rebase --root --exec 'bash scripts/rewrite-commit-identity.sh'
```
